As shown in Table 1, many bismuth metals and its composites have been developed in recent years for application in the anode of PIBs. At present, the preparation methods of metallic bismuth and its composites mainly include pyrolysis and carbothermal reduction method, thermal treatment, electrospinning method, hydrothermal method, ultrasonication-assisted electrochemical exfoliation method and etching method. Overall, the above strategies can effectively improve the main problems currently faced by metal Bi. However, it is worth noting that although the composite of metal Bi with other conductive materials can effectively improve the conductivity of the material, the intrinsic conductivity of the metal Bi itself will not be changed, and therefore it must be designed from an atomic point of view, such as doping or defects, in order to improve the conductivity and thus enhance the electrochemical properties of the material.Table 1
